article.headline: CS Bakersfield 83, Pacific 53
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Issiah Grayson scored 22 points, including 6-of-7 from 3-point range, to lift Cal State-Bakersfield to an 83-53 victory over Pacific on Thursday night. Cal-State Bakersfield (6-6) snapped a four-game losing streak. The Roadrunners used three 3-point baskets, including two by Grayson, to build an early 9-0 lead and never looked back. The team made 15 of 24 from long range on the night. Pacific hit just 10 of 25 shots in the first half and finished with only 17 field goals for the game, including seven 3-pointers. Zach Lamb chipped in with 13 points for Cal State-Bakersfield, while Donald Johnson added 12. Johnson also had eight rebounds. Ross Rivera scored 14 points to lead Pacific (4-6), and Andrew Bock scored 10.
